<hr />

<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

<p>Chaos Engineering is an evolution to business continuity and service resiliency planning. It is the discipline of experimenting on a service to build confidence in its ability to withstand failure in production. Chaos Engineering aims to introduce failures within a system to identify and fix failures proactively before they impact business operations.</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th style="text-align: center"><strong>Chaos Engineering</strong></th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
